group.title: family history
group.text: This module asks about your family’s medical history. Understanding these medical issues can tell us a lot about what kinds of medical issues might be related to your genetics.

question.text: Do you know your family’s medical history? Please include only those family members you are related to by blood.

extension.valueString: ¿Conoce sus antecedentes médicos familiares? Solo piense en los miembros de su familia con los que tenga un vínculo de sangre.

question.text: QUESTION LABEL WAS NOT DEFINED, PLEASE CONTACT ADMINISTRATOR

option.display: head and neck (this includes cancers of the mouth, sinuses, nose, or throat. this does not include brain cancer.)

extension.valueString: Cabeza y cuello (Esto incluye cáncer de boca, seno paranasal, nasal o de garganta. No incluye cáncer de cerebro).

option.display: atrial fibrillation (or a-fib) or atrial flutter (or a-flutter). (these conditions cause irregular, often fast, heart beats that can cause poor blood flow. a-fib and a-flutter are not the same as a heart murmur.)

extension.valueString: Fibrilación auricular (o FA) o palpitación auricular (o PA). (Estas afecciones pueden generar latidos cardíacos irregulares, generalmente rápidos, que pueden producir un flujo sanguíneo insuficiente. La FA y la PA no son lo mismo que un soplo cardíaco).
Enfermedad de la arterias coronarias/coronaria (incluida la angina de pecho)

option.display: pulmonary embolism or deep vein thrombosis (dvt)

extension.valueString: Embolia pulmonar o trombosis venosa profunda (TVP)

option.display: type 1 diabetes (type 1 diabetics do not produce enough insulin on their own, so they have get insulin injections. type 1 diabetes used to be called juvenile onset diabetes.)

extension.valueString: Diabetes tipo 1 (los diabéticos tipo 1 no producen suficiente insulina por sí mismos, por lo que tienen que recibir inyecciones de insulina. La diabetes tipo 1 solía llamarse diabetes juvenil).

option.display: type 2 diabetes (type 1 diabetics do not produce enough insulin on their own, so they have get insulin injections. type 1 diabetes used to be called juvenile onset diabetes. )

extension.valueString: Otro tipo de diabetes conocido/desconocido (Esto incluye diabetes gestacional [diabetes durante el embarazo] y diabetes latente [prediabetes]).
